SECTION 3: WHY THE MISS IS LARGE
----------------------------------------------------------------------

  The sin2_tW prediction (PHYS-27) missed by 1.2%%.
  The alpha_s prediction misses by 12%%. Why the asymmetry?

  sin2_tW is a RATIO of couplings: alpha_1/alpha_2.
  The one-loop errors in alpha_1 and alpha_2 partially cancel.

  alpha_s is the ABSOLUTE value of the third coupling.
  The full Delta = -1.17 translates directly into alpha_s.

    Delta(1/alpha_3) at M_GUT (dimensionless) -63.396668893
    This IS the one-loop Delta from PHYS-24 (dimensionless) -1.17

    Predicted 1/alpha_3 - measured 1/alpha_3 at M_Z (dimensionless) 1.1718059457
    This equals Delta propagated to M_Z (dimensionless) 1.1718059457

  1/alpha_3 too high => alpha_s too low => 12%% miss.

